1. In Today's ever-changing international landscape, most of us observe the importance of perserving our own distinctive cultural heritage.

2. Sadly, because of the expansion of cities and the decrease of natural habitats, falconry is now threatened.

3. According to Barker(2018), in this age of swift globalization, young people who are interested in learing about the customs of their forefather,
	may already be too late to preserve much of our varied and precious cultural heritage

